FT  14 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Malaya Pounds 0.15m in red despite growth
Malaya Group, the USM-quoted motor retailer, reported pre-tax losses of
Pounds 153,000 after a further six months of its planned expansion.
Turnover advanced from Pounds 3.66m to Pounds 15m with gross profits of
Pounds 1.83m against Pounds 518,000. However, operating losses were Pounds
82,000 (profits Pounds 15,000) mainly resulting from the costs of expansion.
Net interest costs were lower at Pounds 71,000 (Pounds 175,000).
Losses per share were reduced at 0.35p (1.87p) after the increase in shares
resulting from the Pounds 9.6m placing and open offer in June.
